metadata.description:
R Hall: Drivers of North Atlantic Jet Stream Vaiability, 1870-2014

The North Atlantic jet stream shows considerable interannual variability. Much of this is due to internal atmospehric variability. However, there are a number of potential drivers of this variability, which are capable of nudging the jet stream. The research aims to identify these drivers scross all four seasons.

This Frostbyte was made by Richard J Hall for the Writing workshop "Linkage between Arctic Climate Change and Mid-latitude Weather Extremes". 2-7 September 2014 Seattle, WA, USA

metadata.description:
http://riddle-of-the-red-bible.webeden.co.uk/ - This video presentation is based on the sci-fi novel I wrote, Riddle of the Red Bible. It is now on sale at various online bookshops such as Amazon.com and Barnes and Noble, to name a few.

The 368-page book was released in July 11th 2012, and published by CC Creative Publishing. 

The novel tells the story of Courtney Nivots, a teenage girl longing to see her deceased father. She encounters an apparition at home which disturbed her and destroyed a cherished porcelain figurine -- a keepsake from her dead father and the only remaining link to her father's memory. 

Courtney sets out to find the answers to her life's questions. She meets Professor Pik Thistle, a renowned American physicist working at Los Tech University in California, where she was hired as researcher. She then discovers a cryptic red book that could somehow answer her questions and make that possible. With the help of some friends, she sets out on a new journey, a perilous adventure to discover the answers to all her questions. 

The novel is set in the Hertfordshire suburb in London, in Manila in the Philippines, and in Los Angeles, California.
